;; clj-kondo config for orca_clj.
;;
;; We keep all bug-catching linters at their defaults (unused vars/requires,
;; shadowed vars, type hints, arity, etc.) and only adjust three stylistic ones
;; that fight this codebase's conventions:
;;   - line-length: relaxed 80 -> 100; numeric data maps are column-aligned.
;;   - docstring-no-summary: docstrings here are rich multi-line explanations,
;;     not a single terminating-period summary line.
;;   - missing-docstring: constants (lat/lon, ordinal maps, formatters) and
;;     -main are self-describing; namespaces carry the prose.
{:linters {:line-length {:max-line-length 100}
           :docstring-no-summary {:level :off}
           :missing-docstring {:level :off}}}
